		<div class="comment-body"><p>Yeah Keyline is just another tool, like swales and terraces. I only really understood how powerful it was after seeing a plow in action and then visiting a farm that had been plowed for the full three years. With every year going deeper, than the year before. The topsoil was so soft, the pastures were lush green while the nieghbours were dead or dormant, and there were springs, this was in a 500mm (on a good year) a year rainfall area.</p>
