	<li class="comment odd alt thread-even depth-1" id="li-comment-227493">
		<div id="comment-227493">
		<div class="comment-author vcard">
			<img alt='' src='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/8b50b10cc1c04e2352e0ef1bdf3e2226?s=48&amp;d=identicon&amp;r=G' class='avatar avatar-48 photo' height='48' width='48' />
			<cite class="fn">David M</cite>

			<span class="comment-meta commentmetadata">
				|
				<a href="http://www.thesurvivalpodcast.com/calls-for-12-7-12/comment-page-1#comment-227493">
				December 15, 2012 at 11:26 am</a>
					|
													</span><!-- .comment-meta .commentmetadata -->
		</div><!-- .comment-author .vcard -->
		
		<div class="comment-body"><p>Great show. A couple ideas.</p>
<p>1) Learn to make Biodiesel. Either through algae, switch grass, etc. Youtube has some videos on this. IMHO it&#8217;s not something I&#8217;m seeing a lot of discussion about. If we have a deep collapse people won&#8217;t be needing a tank a week. Just enough for the farmers market once a month. Or a farmer might need enough for planting a new crop seasonally. People would probably kill for one gallon.</p>
<p>2) Basic electronics. If you have the components and the plans. You could make radios for people. Maybe even powered by a Potato. Add to that a 1 watt transmitter and you could have your own little radio station. People could trade food for advertising.</p>
<p>David M</p>
</div>

